customTrackingEventProcessingFailed

open suspend fun customTrackingEventProcessingFailed(name: String, url: String, error: AdError): AdEventListener.FailureAction

A method for notifying about failed renderer custom tracking event processing.

Note: If you do not use custom renderers, you can ignore this method.

When using custom renderers, you can send your own custom tracking events. An example would be a click on an element inside an ad, or the progress of a viewing the ad. In this case, the app will receive notifications about such events failing using this method.

To learn how to create custom renderer, you can check out our tutorials.

Return

The decision to ignore the error or try the processing again.

Parameters

name

The name of the custom tracking event.

url

The URL that SDK was failed to process.

error

The AdError that occurred during processing.
